messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Fire emergency!
What city are you in?
Daypoint.
Is this a house?
Yes, house upstairs.
What's going on?
The bedroom is on fire. My house is burning fast!
Okay, we're on the way. Just calm down. Is anybody upstairs?
I am, and I can't get down.
You can't get down?
No.
Okay. Anybody else in the house?
Yeah, but I don't know where they're at now.
How old are you?
The room you're in, is it on fire?
No, it's the other end of the house.
Okay. Can you crawl and get down any way at all?
I'm outside on the deck.
You're outside on the deck. Okay. Can you put any towels or anything under the door to keep the smoke out?
I can't get the door shut. It's blown out. My hair is fried.
What floor are you on?
I'm on the second floor.
Is the deck in the front of the house or back of the house?
Back of the house upstairs.
Okay. The back of the house, you copy, Sheriff?
Just stay with me, okay? I want you to get as far away from that door as you can.
I am, I am.
I'm calling the fire department right now. Use the wall for protection.
What?
Use the wall for protection. Get down and use the wall for protection.
Okay, hold on one second.
Hold on one second, okay?
It's burning like crazy.
Is there anybody who has a ladder they can use to help you get down?
There's somebody with a ladder right now.
Okay, stay away from where the fire is. Can you get down safely?
Okay, I'm coming down now.
Okay, thank you. The fire department and the sheriffs are both en route.
Are there any people downstairs?
Confirm if everyone else from downstairs is out.
There are some people downstairs. I think it's her husband. I hope my cat is too.
Make sure everybody is out of the house.
Okay, did she get down?
Ma'am, did you get down safely?
Yes, I'm down. I'm going to open the side gate.
Stay out front. You mentioned getting burned a little bit from your hair. Just sit down and try to relax.
I don't know where my cat is.
Don't worry about the cat. The cat will find its way out. How old are you?
Okay, let them know I'm the one who was on the balcony.
Let them know that you were the one on the balcony and that you might be slightly burned.
Are those the paramedics or sheriffs?
Ma'am, just confirm it's your house.
Yes.
Okay, stay back a little further from the house. What could be burning that badly?
I'm not sure.
Ma'am, I'm going to let you go. I'm very glad you got down safely. Bye-bye.
